      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good - Let’s start with a small blind",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "To a novice, poker can seem pretty daunting with all the rules and intricate strategies, not to mention having to memorise which hands are great and which ones are less than stellar. A big strength of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Poker Club",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is how easy it is to always have access to the information you need at any point through the helpful UI. It’s fairly easy to just hop into a table and start playing, taking small breaks to familiarise yourself with some of the rules as you play.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And speaking of tables, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Poker Club",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " also takes the time to give some pizzazz to the play. Card games aren’t exactly visual spectacles and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Poker Club",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is definitely not winning any awards for best graphics, but the given background context of playing high stakes poker in a hidden club, a high end cassino or the back room of a rundown pizzeria in the single-player campaign certainly helps one get into the mindset of rising through the ranks and making it big through their skills. The ambitious 200+ player tournaments that can be hosted on the online modes also have their own sense of grandeur. Who doesn’t want to be a grand champion and make out like a bandit with millions in poker chips?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Among single-player and big tournaments, there are plenty of other ways to play poker within the game. There are multiple variations of the card game in real life and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Poker Club",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " attempts to tackle plenty of different ways to play poker - specifically, Texas Hold’em variations -  giving players more than enough opportunity to explore the possibilities of the card game.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
